# [[some]]; ''the singular prevocalic partitive article''
#: {{uxi|fr|Voudriez-vous '''de l’'''ail ?|Would you like '''some''' garlic?}}

====Usage notes====
* While English does have the partitive determiner {{m|en|some}}, the French article {{m|fr||de l’-}} frequently translates to nothing at all in English; for example, the above example « Voudriez-vous '''de l’'''ail ? » could also be translated simply as “Would you like garlic?”
